Privacy Policy

This Privacy Policy governs the manner in which Dog Park VR handles user data and ensures compliance with data protection standards.

Information We Collect

Dog Park VR collects limited personal identification information from Users, including IP addresses and microphone access. This information is solely used for the following purposes:

Banning Purposes: User IP addresses and microphone access are collected to enforce community guidelines and ensure fair play within the game.

Voice Chat: Dog Park VR includes a voice chat feature that requires microphone access for communication during gameplay. User voice data is transmitted securely and is not stored beyond the duration of the gameplay session.

How We Use Collected Information

We use the collected information for the following purposes:

Improving User Experience: Data collected helps us understand how users interact with the game, allowing us to enhance their experience.

Community Safety: Information collected aids in enforcing community guidelines and maintaining a safe gaming environment.

User Data Deletion

Users have the right to request the deletion of their collected or stored data. To initiate a data deletion request, users can contact us at electricyt602@gmail.com. Upon receiving a request, we will promptly delete the user's data in accordance with applicable regulations.

Data Protection Checks

Dog Park VR and its organization are committed to upholding data protection standards. We regularly review and update our Privacy Policy to ensure compliance with relevant laws and regulations. Additionally, we implement measures to safeguard user data against unauthorized access, alteration, disclosure, or destruction.

Contact Us

If you have any questions or concerns about our Privacy Policy or data handling practices, please contact us at electricyt602@gmail.com.

This Privacy Policy was last updated on May 28, 2024.
